OL,6,FIn his written evidence, Mr Hall
OL,7,Fclaimed that a video was taken minutes
OL,8,Fafter the blast, showing no damage to
OL,9,Fthe building or broken glass.
OL,11,FDiscussing the video, said to have
OL,12,Fbeen taken by a member of the public
OL,13,Fcalled John Barr, Mr Hall said: "There
OL,14,Fwas no shrapnel visible. The lighting
OL,15,Fwas intact and working. No injuries
OL,16,Fwere visible.
OL,18,F"The number of people in the room
OL,19,Fseemed far lower than officially
OL,20,Fclaimed.
